</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5mp0ZLm.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/s8gyzZ3.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>UPDATE on Kohen Wiley: The community of Senatobia, Mississippi responded to a baby being shot dead in a Walmart parking lot the way communities should — they stopped going. That parking lot should have hundreds of cars. It has almost NONE. This is what organized grief looks like. 

The officer who fired into a vehicle carrying a ONE YEAR OLD — whose mother says she held him UP to show police there was a baby in the car — has been placed on administrative leave. Administrative. Leave. WITH PAY. A baby is in the ground and the shooter gets a PAID FUCKING VACATION. 

Watch that parking lot video. A police cruiser drives slowly through an almost completely empty Walmart on a day it should be packed. The community didn't riot. Didn't burn anything. They just. Stopped. Spending. Their money there. Non-violent, organized, devastating. And the cop car just keeps circling. 

