tle>Happy Midsummer</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dIgjMzU</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dNg9fDO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hell yeah! Today Sweden celebrates its favorite holiday midsommarafton [Midsummer's Eve]</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xbPy8Re.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Clad in flowers and green the midsommarstång [Midsummer pole] is a version of the Maypole, that perhaps originated in Iron Age paganism, who knows? Though while there is no historical basis to claim that it is a penis it is fun to tell people so</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UH0JYpN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Often we forget to please the weather gods, but it's alright. No less as we for the most part are in our own chosen company (it is not a holiday with the relatives like Christmas, instead many are just spending it with friends, old and new)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TcfzlUJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We dance around the pole, mainly for the sake of the little ones. The most popular song - with obligatory jumps - is Små Grodorna [The Little Frogs]. 

It began as a French revolutionary song, La Chanson de l’Oignon [The Onion Song], that presumably via an English parody came to Sweden in the 19th century</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9spvmks.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The main paraphernalia are flowers and leaves woven into a blomsterkrans [flower wreath]. Also it is said that if you pick seven flowers from seven meadows and put them under your pillow at night you will dream of the person you will marry</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vVT30q4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some fancy folk go all in and wear traditional, provincial costumes</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f1w9kFy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>With po-ta-toes. Just as on Christmas. And on Easter</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FfOX8bN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And then strawberries, with cream or ice cream. Or on a cake. Or just a handful. You do you</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1r07XrF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tradition states that before we drink a shot of snaps, we sing a snaps shanty together</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MzsmP8u.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I wish Glad Midsommar to you all, wherever you may be</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dIgjMzU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ngugi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>And just to humiliate you losers further, here is $300 billion</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/W3OGSyO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xg88HCQ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/W3OGSyO</guid